Key Match Events: Germany's 21-year-old forward Maximilian Beier almost scored with his first shot in international soccer, striking the underside of the bar in the 60th minute.
Germany's Maximilian Beier was denied three minutes later by goalkeeper Anatoliy Trubin’s diving save, then he sent a stooping header wide of the goal.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The head of Germany’s federal government, Chancellor Olaf Scholz, was at the game in Nuremberg, which is not among the 10 Euro 2024 venues.
